        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 5 at 2:35AM MDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 234 AM MDT, strong thunderstorms were developing along a line
extending from 11 miles south of Mott to 11 miles north of Thunder
Hawk. Movement was north at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mott and Regent.
</description>
        <instruction>These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
